c forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Swillington","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Lancashire):","habitational name from Shilvington in Morpeth (Northumberland). The placename probably means something like ‘the farmstead of the people who live at the ledge’, from Old English <i>scelf</i> ‘rock, ledge, shelf’ + the groupname suffix <i>-ingas</i> (genitive <i>-inga-</i>) + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’.","perhaps a habitational name from Shitlington (Yorkshire), from an Old English personal name <i>Scyt(t)el</i> + Old English connective <i>-ing-</i> + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert de Swillington was born in 1152, in Well, Yorkshire, England, his father, Hugh de Swillington, was 27 and his mother, Lady Hugh de Swillington, was 22. He had at least 2 sons. He died in 1180, in Yorkshire, England, at the age of 28."},"et":{"1152–1180":"1152–1180","1155–Female":"1155–Surnud","1175–Male":"1175–Surnud","1177–Male":"1177–Surnud","1125–Male":"1125–Surnud","1130–Female":"1130–Surnud","1125":"1125","1177":"1177","1155":"1155","1175":"1175","1152":"1152","1130":"1130","1180":"1180","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Well, Yorkshire, England":"Well, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"1152–1180":"1152–1180","1155–Female":"1155–Kuollut","1175–Male":"1175–Kuollut","1177–Male":"1177–Kuollut","1125–Male":"1125–Kuollut","1130–Female":"1130–Kuollut","1125":"1125","1177":"1177","1155":"1155","1175":"1175","1152":"1152","1130":"1130","1180":"1180","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Well, Yorkshire, England":"Well, Yorkshire, England"},"fr":{"1152–1180":"1152–1180","1155–Female":"1155–Décédée","1175–Male":"1175–Décédé","1177–Male":"1177–Décédé","1125–Male":"1125–Décédé","1130–Female":"1130–Décédée","1125":"1125","1177":"1177","1155":"1155","1175":"1175","1152":"1152","1130":"1130","1180":"1180","Yorkshire, England":"Everwyck, Angleterre","Well, Yorkshire, England":"Well, Everwyck, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Robert de Swillington est né en 1152, à Well, Everwyck, Angleterre, son père, Hugh de Swillington, avait 27 ans et sa mère, Lady Hugh de Swillington, avait 22 ans. Il a eu au moins 2 fils. Il est décédé en 1180, à Everwyck, Angleterre, à l’âge de 28 ans."},"de":{"1152–1180":"1152–1180","1155–Female":"1155–Verstorben","1175–Male":"1175–Verstorben","1177–Male":"1177–Verstorben","1125–Male":"1125–Verstorben","1130–Female":"1130–Verstorben","1125":"1125","1177":"1177","1155":"1155","1175":"1175","1152":"1152","1130":"1130","1180":"1180","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Well, Yorkshire, England":"We